{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban unsolicited mail, unwanted marketing material, leaflets and flyers",
        "additional_details": "I live in a modest terraced house and I\u2019m sick and tired of my home being bombarded by material I don't want to receive. Existing schemes requiring registration every two years (which is a pain) don't deal with casual leafleting and Royal Mail's excuse of a \u2018contractual obligation\u2019 to continue to deliver mass produced addressed and \u2018to the occupier\u2019 marketing material, when it's unwanted is unacceptable.\r\n\r\nThose that wish to receive junk mail etc, simply don't put the sticker on their letterbox.",
        "background": "Introduce a bill to make it a fineable offence to post leaflets, flyers, or unsolicited addressed and \u2018to the occupier\u2019 or similar mass-produced marketing mail, to domestic or commercial properties with letterboxes marked with a catch-all \u2018No junk Mail\u2019 sticker.",
